<paragraph id="8BF9368F292EFFB020FFE18E9475951D" blockId="5.[136,1452,954,1120]" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">
Recognised in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D0C292EFFB021F5E18E969292CA" authorityName="Forsskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[386,450,954,975]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Maesa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="5" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EA9D292EFFB021F5E18E969292CA" box="[386,450,954,975]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="250">Maesa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: scrambling habit, entire leaf margins and most parts conspicuously pubescent with striking, ginger-brown hairs together with scales, leaves drying dark sage-green adaxially and reddish brown abaxially, and cladodromous–eucamptodromus venation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
